docs.lead_paragraph: For a country where smoking is everywhere and obesity and diabetes are rampant, a new fitness revolution has been a stark departure.
docs.abstract: Fitness craze has taken hold in Egypt in aftermath of Arab Spring uprising and military crackdown that put Abdel Fattah el-Sisi in power, as young people turn their focus from public sphere to private activity; many Egyptians see workout trend as direct outgrowth of withering political revolution under Pres Sisi, who has in turn encouraged fad.

headline.main: Egyptians Take to the Streets Again, Now in Workout Gear
headline.print_headline: Egyptians Take to the Streets Again, This Time in Workout Gear
